you like.

I do not call myself a &quot;Stratfordian&quot;; I do not have different procedures
for evaluating the evidence for Shakespeare's authorship of his works than
I would use for other authors, but I know of no antistratfordian &quot;case&quot;
that is not based on the use of special interpretive rules and special
pleading.

In some ways, the &quot;Bacon wrote everything&quot; (and its parody the &quot;Oxford
