antistratfordians. Given that antistratfordians must replace the methods
used by genuine literary historians with whatever they find in their own
toolkits, it is inevitable that some will ask, &quot;what if we apply the
methods we use to prove that X wrote Shakespeare to authors other than
Shakespeare?&quot; Since those methods generate false positives for
Shakespeare, they may also generate false positives for other writers as
well (&quot;what do you know -- X was not only Shakespeare but also Golding,
Nashe, Sidney, Lyly, Spenser, Drayton, Greene, etc.&quot;).

