Stella*, Spenser's *Amoretti*, Drayton's *Idea*, and *Shakespeare's
Sonnets* were all written by the same person; if he were less impaired by
his emotional commitment to antistratfordianism, he might have the wit to
realize that the more different authors his methods show were really
Oxford, the more he demonstrates the utter worthlessness of those methods
and his own limitations as a reader.

