Jesting aside, I can't let this utter rubbish pass. Nabokov certainly
ridiculed two Jewish *individuals*, Marx and Freud, relentlessly, but his
contempt for Marx and Freud had *nothing whatever* to do with their
ethnic origin. Indeed, Nabokov, like his father, was an eloquent and
outspoken foe of anti-Semitism, and indeed of racism in various forms;
in particular, he spoke out forcefully against anti-Semitism on many,
many occasions, and even incurred considerable personal risk by openly
defying the Nazis' attempts to intimidate the non-Jewish population into
boycotting Jewish business establishments. Nabokov's wife Vera Slonim
was Jewish, and Nabokov's family history, particularly his father's
